The '''Mount Bold Football Club''' was a shortly-lived [[Australian rules football]] club that was established in 1962 as a merger between the [[Kangarilla Football Club]] and the [[Clarendon Football Club]], initially playing in the [[Hills Central Football Association]].<ref name=EOSACFC-MtBold>{{cite book|last=Lines|first=Peter|title=Encyclopedia of South Australian Country Football Clubs|year=2008|publisher=Peter Lines|location=[[Cowell, South Australia]]|isbn=978-0-9804472-9-3|page=164}}</ref>  <br />

In 1964, Mount Bold transferred to the [[Southern Football League (South Australia)|Southern Football League]].  In the 1964 and 1965 seasons, Mount Bold failed to qualify for finals and disbanded at the end of the 1965 season with [[Kangarilla Football Club|Kangarilla]] reforming.<ref>{{cite news|last=Garvis|first=Sarah|title=Bold Cameo|url=http://digitaledition.southerntimes.com.au/?xml=Southern_Times_Messenger&iid=46205|accessdate=17 July 2013|newspaper=Southern Times Messenger|date=9 March 2011|page=8}}</ref>   [[Clarendon Football Club|Clarendon]] never re-established.<ref name=EOSACFC-MtBold />

